{{Infobox person |name = Eurípedes Barsanulfo |image = Euripedes Barsanulfo Sacramento2.jpg |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date|1880|5|1}} |birth_place = [[Sacramento, Minas Gerais]], [[Brazil]] |death_date = {{Death date and age|1918|11|1|1880|5|1}} |death_place = Sacramento, Minas Gerais, Brazil |occupation = Educator, politician}}
'''Eurípedes Barsanulfo''', (May 1, 1880 – November 1, 1918) was a Brazilian [[educator]], [[pharmacist]], [[politician]] and prominent [[Spiritism|spiritist]] [[mediumship|medium]]. He is best known as the founder and first headmaster of Colégio [[Allan Kardec]], one of the first spiritist schools in the world.
